---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import EmailSignup from '../components/EmailSignup.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Pairing · A 12-book YA fantasy series by Caleb Arlow"
  description="Inside The Pairing: the thread system, the Threadweavers, the four-arc structure, and what is coming next. No spoilers past Book Three."
>
  <PageHero eyebrow="Inside the series">
    <Fragment slot="title">
      The world of <span class="em-italic">The Pairing.</span>
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="lead">
      A magic system, a regime, and a girl whose thread doesn't have a color the regime admits exists.
    </Fragment>
  </PageHero>

  <!-- Threads -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-text">
      <p class="t-eyebrow">The thread system</p>
      <h2 class="t-h2" style="margin: var(--s-3) 0 var(--s-5);">Every bond shows up as a thread.</h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        Every citizen is paired at thirteen. The bond between two people manifests as a colored thread, and the color tells the system what kind of love it is dealing with. Gold is rare. Red is monitored. Gray means the system has interfered. White is not supposed to exist.
      </p>
      <p class="body-text">
        Threads are made from veilsilk, a substance harvested from the boundary between worlds. It is the magic in the magic system, and the people in charge are running out of it.
      </p>
      <p class="body-text">
        A small number of people can read the threads directly. Lira is one. The Threadweavers know this is dangerous. They have known for a long time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Four arcs -->
  <section class="section section-tinted">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div style="text-align: center; max-width: 56ch; margin: 0 auto var(--s-7);">
        <p class="t-eyebrow silver" style="justify-content: center;">Structure</p>
        <h2 class="t-h2" style="margin: var(--s-3) 0 var(--s-4);">Four arcs. Twelve books.</h2>
        <p class="body-text">
          The series is built in four three-book arcs. Each arc moves the story forward and asks one core question.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="arc-grid">
        <article class="arc-card">
          <p class="arc-num">Arc One</p>
          <h3 class="arc-title">Discovery <span class="arc-books">(Books 1-3)</span></h3>
          <p class="arc-q">Can you be truly seen without being destroyed?</p>
          <p class="arc-blurb">
            Lira meets Tieran, finds out what her thread is, and learns the difference between protection and surveillance. Ages 13-14. The arc closes with a choice that breaks the world open.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="arc-card">
          <p class="arc-num">Arc Two</p>
          <h3 class="arc-title">Rebellion <span class="arc-books">(Books 4-6)</span></h3>
          <p class="arc-q">Can love survive a movement?</p>
          <p class="arc-blurb">
            Two years later. The resistance has a name. Lira and Tieran are inside it. What started as a private bond becomes a public symbol, and symbols draw fire.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="arc-card">
          <p class="arc-num">Arc Three</p>
          <h3 class="arc-title">Transformation <span class="arc-books">(Books 7-9)</span></h3>
          <p class="arc-q">What does love look like after the war ends?</p>
          <p class="arc-blurb">
            Victory is partial. Loss is not. The arc moves from rebellion to rebuilding, and asks whether the people who tore the system down can avoid becoming the next version of it.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="arc-card">
          <p class="arc-num">Arc Four</p>
          <h3 class="arc-title">Legacy <span class="arc-books">(Books 10-12)</span></h3>
          <p class="arc-q">What do the next ones do with what we left them?</p>
          <p class="arc-blurb">
            A new pairing. A new generation. A world that has changed and not changed at the same time. The arc closes the series and answers the original question with the wisdom of having lived through it.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reader on-ramp -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-text">
      <p class="t-eyebrow">Where to start</p>
      <h2 class="t-h2" style="margin: var(--s-3) 0 var(--s-5);">Read in order.</h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        The Pairing is a continuous story. Start at Book One. The discovery arc is three books, and they are designed to be read together. The Rebellion arc opens with Book Four.
      </p>

      <div class="reading-list">
        <a href="/books/thread-of-gold" class="reading-row">
          <span class="reading-num">01</span>
          <span class="reading-title">Thread of Gold</span>
          <span class="reading-stat">Out now</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/books/thread-of-silver" class="reading-row">
          <span class="reading-num">02</span>
          <span class="reading-title">Thread of Silver</span>
          <span class="reading-stat">Out now</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/books/thread-of-white" class="reading-row">
          <span class="reading-num">03</span>
          <span class="reading-title">Thread of White</span>
          <span class="reading-stat">Out now</span>
        </a>
        <div class="reading-row reading-row-locked">
          <span class="reading-num">04</span>
          <span class="reading-title">The next book</span>
          <span class="reading-stat coming">Coming next</span>
        </div>
        <div class="reading-row reading-row-locked">
          <span class="reading-num">05–12</span>
          <span class="reading-title">The rest of the series</span>
          <span class="reading-stat">Revealed one at a time</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Email signup -->
  <section class="section section-tinted">
    <div class="wrap">
      <EmailSignup
        headline="The series unlocks here, in order."
        sub="Each new book is announced to the newsletter first. Cover, title, release date. Then everywhere else."
      />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .arc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--s-5);
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .arc-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .arc-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--thread-gold);
    padding: var(--s-6);
  }
  .arc-card:nth-child(2) { border-left-color: var(--thread-silver); }
  .arc-card:nth-child(3) { border-left-color: var(--thread-white); }
  .arc-card:nth-child(4) { border-left-color: var(--thread-gold-2); }
  .arc-num {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.32em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--thread-gold);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-2);
  }
  .arc-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--paper-50);
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin-bottom: var(--s-3);
  }
  .arc-books {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .arc-q {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--paper-100);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-3);
  }
  .arc-blurb {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
  }

  .reading-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    margin-top: var(--s-6);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }
  .reading-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 60px 1fr auto;
    gap: var(--s-4);
    align-items: center;
    padding: var(--s-4) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    transition: background var(--dur-base) var(--ease-out);
  }
  a.reading-row:hover { background: rgba(201, 168, 97, 0.04); }
  .reading-num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--thread-gold);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .reading-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--paper-50);
  }
  .reading-row-locked .reading-title { color: var(--fg-muted); }
  .reading-stat {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--paper-300);
  }
  .reading-stat.coming { color: var(--thread-gold); }
</style>
